<p>I have a bunch of repeated code sitewide on div's that I'd like to replace with another tag. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-group" ng-show="!loadingText"&gt;    &lt;label&gt;Status&lt;/label&gt;    &lt;div class="form-control" ng-if="request.RequestStatus"&gt;       {{ request.RequestStatus }}    &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   </code></pre>  <p>What would be a good way though out the site to replace the opening and closing <code>div</code> tags that match <code>&lt;div class="form-group" ng-show="!loadingText"&gt;</code>, while preserving the content between the tags?</p>  <p>The replacement that I'm looking to do would be result in the following:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;fg&gt;    &lt;label&gt;Status&lt;/label&gt;    &lt;div class="form-control" ng-if="request.RequestStatus"&gt;       {{ request.RequestStatus }}    &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/fg&gt;    </code></pre>